  <!-- ====== FAQ ====== -->
  <section class="lo-faq" id="help">
    <div class="lo-faq-inner">
      <div class="lo-faq-header">
        <div class="lo-section-eyebrow">Questions</div>
        <h2 class="lo-section-headline">Things parents <em>ask us</em></h2>
      </div>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>What exactly is a .com domain, and why does my child need one?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">A .com domain is a unique address on the internet — like "your-childs-name.com." Only one person can own each address. When you claim your child's name as a .com, nobody else in the world can ever use that exact address. As they grow up, it becomes their homepage, their portfolio, their identity on the internet. And you'll have started it for them before they could even walk.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>What if my child's exact name isn't available?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">You can get creative — add a middle name, a family name, or a nickname. Search variations right here on the site. Many parents use formats like firstnamelastname.com, babyfirstname.com, or even a family surname. There's almost always a great option available.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>What does the book actually look like?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">It's a beautiful, private website at their .com — like a personal magazine for your family. It has sections for birth story, month-by-month milestones, unlimited photos, letters to your child, family recipes, and a sealed Time Vault for messages to open when they're older. You can see a real example using the "Live Demo" link in the features section.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>Is the book private? Who can see it?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">Yes — the site is password protected. Only people you share the password with can view it. You control who sees your family's story.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>What happens after the first year?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">After your introductory year at $29, the plan renews at $49.99/year (about $4.17/month). You can cancel anytime from your account — if you cancel, your book goes private but your domain stays registered until it expires. You can always re-activate later.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item">
        <summary>Can I give this as a baby shower gift?</summary>
        <p class="lo-faq-answer">Absolutely — it's one of the most popular ways people use Legacy Odyssey. You buy a gift code for $29, and the recipient redeems it to pick their own domain and set up their book. It arrives as a digital gift code you can print or email.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

